    'Mat pilates focused on core, lumbo-pelvic stability and muscle control. Essential foundation for all dance movements.',

  prepFisica_whichActivity_beginner_title: 'First time in physical preparation? Start here',
  prepFisica_whichActivity_beginner_text:
    "If you've never done physical preparation for dance, start with Stretching (basic flexibility), Body Conditioning (functional strength) or Yoga Flow (control and balance). They are the perfect foundations for any dancer.",

  prepFisica_whichActivity_complement_title: 'How to complement your dance classes?',
  prepFisica_whichActivity_complement_text:
    'Ballet and Contemporary: Stretching + Dance Barre + Pilates. Urban and Dancehall: Body Conditioning + Bum Bum Glúteos. Salsa and Bachata: Yoga Flow + Stretching + Body Conditioning. Combine activities for complete results.',

  prepFisica_whichActivity_combine_title: 'Can I combine several activities?',
  prepFisica_whichActivity_combine_text:
    'Absolutely yes. In fact, we recommend it. The ideal combination: 2-3 dance sessions + 1-2 physical preparation sessions per week. Alternate strength (Body Conditioning) with flexibility (Stretching/Yoga) for balanced development.',

  prepFisica_why_title: "Why train dance at Farray's Center",

  // Why pillars
  prepFisica_why_farray_method_title: 'Farray Method®',
  prepFisica_why_farray_method_content:
    'Exclusive training system created by Yunaisy Farray, Street Dance 2 dancer and internationally recognized master. Combines specific physical preparation for dancers with injury prevention techniques and performance optimization. Fast and safe results.',

  prepFisica_why_specialized_title: 'Specialized Training for Dancers',
  prepFisica_why_specialized_content:
    "It's not generic fitness. Every exercise is designed thinking about dance-specific demands: jumps, turns, extensions, body control. We train movements you use in class.",

  prepFisica_why_injury_title: 'Effective Injury Prevention',
  prepFisica_why_injury_content:
    'We strengthen ankles, knees, hips and core to reduce the risk of common dancer injuries. Corrective work, proprioception and functional exercises that protect your body.',

  prepFisica_why_performance_title: 'Improve Your Class Performance',
  prepFisica_why_performance_content:
    'Jump higher, turn with more control, hold extensions longer, endure complete choreographies without fatigue. Physical preparation translates directly into better technical execution.',

  prepFisica_why_flexibility_title: 'Flexibility and Range of Motion',
  prepFisica_why_flexibility_content:
    'Work on active stretching, PNF and joint mobility to achieve splits, high extensions and wide movements with control. Functional flexibility, not passive.',

  prepFisica_why_strength_title: 'Functional Strength without Bulk',
  prepFisica_why_strength_content:
    'Develop explosive strength and muscular endurance without excessive volume. Training designed to create strong, agile and aesthetic bodies, perfect for dance.',

  prepFisica_why_holistic_title: 'Holistic Mind-Body Approach',
  prepFisica_why_holistic_content:
    "We combine physical training with body awareness, breathing and mental control. You don't just train muscles, you train the complete system that allows you to dance with excellence.",

  // FAQ - Physical Preparation
  prepFisica_faq_title: 'Frequently asked questions about training for dancers',

  prepFisicaFaqQ1: 'What is physical preparation for dancers and how does it differ from the gym?',
  prepFisicaFaqA1:
    "It's specific training designed for dancer needs: explosive strength for jumps, core for turns, active flexibility, endurance for choreographies and injury prevention. Unlike conventional gym, every exercise has direct application in dance.",

  prepFisicaFaqQ2: 'Do I need previous experience in physical training?',
  prepFisicaFaqA2:
    'No. Classes are adapted to all levels. If you dance, you already have the foundation. We teach you correct technique for each exercise from scratch and progress according to your current fitness level.',

  prepFisicaFaqQ3:
    'How many times per week should I train physical preparation if I already take dance classes?',
  prepFisicaFaqA3:
    'Ideal: 2-3 weekly sessions of 45-60 minutes. If you dance 4-5 times per week, 2 physical preparation sessions are enough to see significant improvements in strength, flexibility and injury prevention.',

  prepFisicaFaqQ4: 'Will physical preparation help me prevent injuries?',
  prepFisicaFaqA4:
    'Yes. We strengthen vulnerable areas (ankles, knees, hips, lower back), correct muscle imbalances, improve proprioception and teach safe movement patterns. You drastically reduce the risk of common injuries.',

  prepFisicaFaqQ5: 'Will I gain a lot of muscle volume with this training?',
  prepFisicaFaqA5:
    'No. Training is designed to develop functional strength, explosiveness and muscular endurance without excessive hypertrophy. You get a strong, agile and aesthetic body, perfect for dancing.',

  prepFisicaFaqQ6: 'Can I improve my flexibility with physical preparation?',
  prepFisicaFaqA6:
    "Yes. We include specific flexibility sessions with active stretching, PNF, joint mobility and range of motion exercises. Many students achieve splits and extensions they didn't have before.",

  prepFisicaFaqQ7: 'Will this training help me jump higher and turn better?',
  prepFisicaFaqA7:
    "Absolutely. We work on explosive leg strength for jumps, core and stability for controlled turns, and proprioception for balance. You'll see direct improvements in your dance technique.",

  prepFisicaFaqQ8: 'What clothing and footwear do I need for physical preparation classes?',
  prepFisicaFaqA8:
    'Comfortable sportswear (leggings, technical t-shirt) and training shoes with good cushioning. For flexibility exercises, many prefer to train barefoot or with non-slip socks.',

  prepFisicaFaqQ9: 'Can I combine physical preparation with my dance classes?',
  prepFisicaFaqA9:
    'Yes, highly recommended. Physical preparation complements your dance training: improves technical performance, prevents injuries and accelerates your progress. Many dancers combine 3-4 dance classes + 2 physical preparation weekly.',

  prepFisicaFaqQ10: 'Where are the physical preparation classes held?',
  prepFisicaFaqA10:
    'At our facilities on Calle Entença 100, Barcelona, 5 minutes from Plaza España and Sants. Spacious 700 m² rooms with professional flooring, specific equipment and dance-specialized environment.',

  // Final CTA
  prepFisica_finalCTA_title: 'Transform Your Body, Elevate Your Dance',
  prepFisica_finalCTA_subtitle: 'Train like a professional dancer. Not like a generic athlete.',
  prepFisica_finalCTA_description:
    'Join hundreds of students—from absolute beginners to advanced dancers—who are improving their performance in stretching, body conditioning, pilates, yoga flow, dance barre and much more. All with the exclusive Farray Method® created by Yunaisy Farray (Street Dance 2 dancer) and specialized training for the demands of dance in the heart of Barcelona.',

  // Testimonials - Preparación Física Bailarines
  prepFisica_testimonials_title: 'Unsolicited Testimonials from Our Students',
  prepFisica_testimonials_intro:
    "Dancers who are improving their performance with our specialized training share their authentic experience at Farray's Center Barcelona. No filters, no scripts. Just real stories of physical and technical transformation.",

